parties (such as the Patriot party, a successor to the Jansenist party), whose rhetoric affected the content of revolutionary as well as counterrevolutionary political culture. Even in its dechristianizing phase, says Van Kley, revolutionary political culture was considerably more indebted to varieties of French Catholicism than it realized.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChristianity and politicsxHistory. 0aChurch and statexHistoryx18th centuryxFrance. 0aChurch and statezFrancexHistoryy18th century. 0aSecularismxHistoryx18th centuryxFrance. 0aSecularismzFrancexHistoryy18th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014756840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300147568423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300147568/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles